<p><b>Human Rights Council 
Twentieth session 
</b>Agenda item 3 
<b>Promotion and protection of all human rights, civil, 
political, economic, social and cultural rights, 
including the right to development 
</b></p>
<p><b>  Report of the Special Rapporteur on extreme poverty and 
human rights, Magdalena Sep&#250;lveda Carmona 
</b></p>
<p><b>  Addendum 
</b></p>
<p><b>  Mission to Paraguay (11 to 16 December 2011)</b>*<b> 
</b></p>
<p> <i>Summary</i> 
 At the invitation of the Government of Paraguay, the Special Rapporteur on extreme 
poverty and human rights visited the country from 11 to 16 December 2011. The objective 
of the mission was to examine the enjoyment of human rights on the part of those members 
of the population who are living in extreme poverty and the obstacles standing in the way 
of the achievement of a socially inclusive form of growth. The report focuses on a number 
of flagship programmes, including the Tekopor&#227; conditional cash transfer programme, the 
Abrazo (&#8220;hug&#8221;) Programme and the Family Health Units Programme. The Special 
Rapporteur expresses her appreciation for the Government&#8217;s openness and recognizes that 
major strides have been made in the area of rights-based public policy planning. She also 
recognizes the achievements of the flagship programmes which she reviewed. While 
acknowledging the magnitude of the challenges faced by Paraguay, she expresses concern 
at the presence of striking economic and social inequalities, corruption, a regressive tax 
structure, the high degree of concentration of land ownership and environmental problems 
which seriously interfere with poor people&#8217;s enjoyment of their rights. 
 The report sets forth specific recommendations for ensuring that the human rights of 
persons living in poverty are protected and that an inclusive form of growth is achieved. 
</p>
<p> 
</p>
<p> 
</p>
<p>  
</p>
<p> * The summary of this report is being circulated in all official languages. The report itself, contained in 
the annex to the summary, is being circulated in the language of submission only. 
</p>
